Farmer Dunphy has $$100$$ metres of fencing.  He wants to make a closed rectangular pen.  He uses a long wall for one of the sides.  Each side of the pen is a whole number in metres.  What is the largest area that the pen can be?
(A) 125\text{m}^{2}
(B) 625\text{m}^{2}
(C) 1000\text{m}^{2}
(D) 1250\text{m}^{2}
(E) 2500\text{m}^{2}

Farmer Dunphy has $$16$$ metres of fencing.  He wants to make a closed rectangular pen.  He uses a long wall for one of the sides.  Each side of the pen is a whole number in metres.  What is the largest area that the pen can be?
(A) 25\text{m}^{2}
(B) 27\text{m}^{2}
(C) 30\text{m}^{2}
(D) 28\text{m}^{2}
(E) 32\text{m}^{2}
